From aba0f922b in plasma/breeze (Plasma/6.7 branch)
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Fix SE_ItemViewItemText: remove unconditional horizontal narrowing

Commit aba0f922b ("Make viewItemPrimitive rounded like in QtQuick style",
Akseli Lahtinen, 2026-02-25) added two lines to SE_ItemViewItemText that
unconditionally narrow the text rect by (margins + ItemView_ItemPaddingWidth)
on each side — 4px per side, 8px total.

This discards 8px from the available text width regardless of column
width, causing visible label elision in any list/tree view using the
Breeze style with narrow or medium-width columns.

Affected applications (confirmed via numeric probe and visual verification):
- KeePassXC 2.7.x (Qt5, entry properties panel / sidebar)
- SMPlayer (Qt5, Preferences sidebar when style = Breeze)
- GoldenDict (Qt5, word list pane)

The highlight rect is already inset by itemViewItemMargins (2px/side) in
the highlight paint path. The text rect does not need to mirror that inset;
Qt's base class already allocates space for check indicators and decorations
via SE_ItemViewItemCheckIndicator / SE_ItemViewItemDecoration.

This patch removes both horizontal-narrowing lines and keeps only the
existing vertical adjustment (moveTop) which correctly accounts for
asymmetric top/bottom margins in the rounded highlight geometry.

Probe output before patch (Breeze, SE_ItemViewItemText vs. base rect):
  column 80px:  diff=8   column 120px: diff=8   column 200px: diff=8
  (Fusion/Windows: diff=0 at all widths)

Probe output after patch (Breeze):
  column 80px:  diff=0   column 120px: diff=0   column 200px: diff=0

diff --git a/kstyle/breezestyle.cpp b/kstyle/breezestyle.cpp
--- a/kstyle/breezestyle.cpp
+++ b/kstyle/breezestyle.cpp
@@ -1062,8 +1062,8 @@ QRect Style::subElementRect(SubElement element, const QStyleOption *option, cons
         QRect rect = ParentStyleClass::subElementRect(element, option, widget);
         if (viewItem) {
             const QMargins margins = _helper->itemViewItemMargins(viewItem);
-            rect.setRight(rect.right() - margins.right() - Metrics::ItemView_ItemPaddingWidth);
-            rect.setLeft(rect.left() + margins.left() + Metrics::ItemView_ItemPaddingWidth);
             rect.moveTop(rect.top() + margins.top() - margins.bottom());
         }

